WEBVTT



00:00:00.576 --> 00:00:08.192
Well hello friends and thank you for joining me in our daily reading from God's holy word today we're reading mark chapter 11.

00:00:07.872 --> 00:00:11.552
And in this lesson we see Jesus provocatively

00:00:11.360 --> 00:00:13.600
Make use of his authority.

00:00:14.080 --> 00:00:16.352
Before we read, let's pray.

00:00:16.704 --> 00:00:20.512
Our Father in heaven, show us Jesus.

00:00:20.608 --> 00:00:22.304
In his name I pray.

00:00:22.432 --> 00:00:23.648
Amen.

00:00:24.608 --> 00:00:26.240
Mark chapter eleven.

00:00:26.112 --> 00:00:32.160
Now when they drew near to Jerusalem, to Bethphage and Bethany, at the Mount of Olives,

00:00:32.096 --> 00:00:42.144
Jesus sent two of his disciples and said to them, Go into the village in front of you, and immediately as you enter it, you will find a colt tied, on which note.

00:00:41.664 --> 00:00:43.424
which no one has ever sat.

00:00:43.168 --> 00:00:44.480
I'm tired.

00:00:44.352 --> 00:00:45.568
And bring it.

00:00:45.632 --> 00:00:49.280
And if anyone says to you, "Why are you doing this?"

00:00:49.088 --> 00:00:50.272
Say,

00:00:50.144 --> 00:00:52.192
The Lord has need of it.

00:00:51.936 --> 00:00:54.496
And we'll send it back here immediately.

00:00:54.976 --> 00:01:01.312
And they went away and found a colt tied at the door outside in the street, and they untied it.

00:01:01.440 --> 00:01:05.280
And some of those standing there said to them,

00:01:05.024 --> 00:01:06.592
What are you doing?

00:01:06.528 --> 00:01:08.352
Untying the colt

00:01:08.512 --> 00:01:11.360
And they told them what Jesus had said.

00:01:11.456 --> 00:01:13.024
And they let them go.

00:01:13.312 --> 00:01:23.360
And they brought the colt to Jesus and threw their cloaks on it, and he sat on it. And many spread their cloaks on the road, and others spread leafy branches.

00:01:22.880 --> 00:01:30.432
Anxious that they had cut from the fields and those who went before and those who followed were shouting, Hosanna.

00:01:30.272 --> 00:01:39.776
Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord. Blessed is the coming kingdom of our father David. Hosanna in the highest.

00:01:40.448 --> 00:01:42.240
And he entered Jerusalem.

00:01:42.176 --> 00:01:44.064
And went into the temple.

00:01:44.096 --> 00:01:48.800
And when he had looked around at everything as it was already late,

00:01:48.608 --> 00:01:51.360
He went out to Bethany with the twelve.

00:01:51.488 --> 00:01:55.744
On the following day, when they came from Bethany, he was hungry.

00:01:55.936 --> 00:01:59.680
And seeing in the distance a fig-tree in leaf.

00:01:59.584 --> 00:02:02.496
He went to see if he could find anything on it.

00:02:02.368 --> 00:02:07.360
When he came to it, he found nothing but leaves, for it was not the season for figs.

00:02:07.200 --> 00:02:08.608
And he said to it,

00:02:08.544 --> 00:02:12.576
May no one ever eat fruit from you again.

00:02:12.704 --> 00:02:14.432
And his disciples heard it.

00:02:14.912 --> 00:02:22.272
And they came to Jerusalem, and he entered the temple and began to drive out those who sold and those who bought.

00:02:22.048 --> 00:02:28.960
In the temple, and he overturned the tables of the money changers and the seats of those who sold pigeons.

00:02:28.928 --> 00:02:33.248
And he would not allow anyone to carry anything through the temple.

00:02:33.280 --> 00:02:42.144
And he was teaching them and saying to them, Is it not written, My house shall be called a house of prayer for all the nations?

00:02:42.304 --> 00:02:45.664
But you have made it a den of robbers.

00:02:46.144 --> 00:02:55.840
And the chief priests and the scribes heard it, and were seeking a way to destroy him, for they feared him, because all the crowd was astonished at his teaching.

00:02:55.808 --> 00:02:58.752
And when evening came, they went out of the city.

00:02:59.072 --> 00:03:09.120
And as they passed by in the morning, they saw the fig tree withered away to its roots, and Peter remembered and said to him, Rabbi, look, the fig tree that you cursed has withered.

00:03:08.640 --> 00:03:11.168
is withered, and Jesus answered them, O Lord.

00:03:11.104 --> 00:03:12.864
Have faith in God.

00:03:12.768 --> 00:03:22.816
"'Truly, I say to you, whoever says to this mountain, "'Be taken up and thrown into the sea "'and does not doubt in his heart, "'but believes that what he says will

00:03:22.336 --> 00:03:25.696
says will come to pass, it will be done for him.

00:03:25.600 --> 00:03:33.024
Therefore, I tell you, whatever you ask in prayer, believe that you have received it and it will be yours.

00:03:32.768 --> 00:03:36.192
And whenever you stand praying, forgive.

00:03:35.936 --> 00:03:43.360
If you have anything against anyone, so that your Father also who is in heaven may forgive you your trespasses.

00:03:43.616 --> 00:03:53.664
And they came again to Jerusalem, and as he was walking in the temple, the chief priests and the scribes and the elders came to him, and they said to him, By what authority are you?

00:03:53.184 --> 00:03:58.528
Are you doing these things? And who gave you this authority to do them?

00:03:58.976 --> 00:04:00.832
Jesus said to them,

00:04:00.640 --> 00:04:07.648
I will ask you one question. Answer me, and I will tell you by what authority I do these things.

00:04:07.648 --> 00:04:11.296
Was the baptism of John from heaven?

00:04:11.296 --> 00:04:12.736
Or from man.

00:04:12.800 --> 00:04:14.016
Answer me.

00:04:14.336 --> 00:04:19.296
And they discussed it with one another, saying, "If we say, 'From heaven,

00:04:19.264 --> 00:04:22.144
He will say, then why did you not believe him?

00:04:22.464 --> 00:04:25.632
But shall we say from man

00:04:25.760 --> 00:04:27.648
They were afraid of the people.

00:04:27.424 --> 00:04:30.656
For they all held that John really was a prophet.

00:04:30.816 --> 00:04:34.240
So they answered Jesus, "We do not know."

00:04:34.240 --> 00:04:39.744
And Jesus said to them, "Neither will I tell you by one authority I do these things."

00:04:40.128 --> 00:04:41.568
Amen. This is

00:04:41.248 --> 00:04:43.008
God's word

00:04:43.008 --> 00:04:51.072
This chapter is woven around three events in which Jesus very deliberately calls attention to himself.

00:04:50.976 --> 00:04:52.576
To invite us

00:04:52.448 --> 00:04:54.752
To ask, who is he?

00:04:55.008 --> 00:05:04.704
The first event is Jesus coming into Jerusalem. The second is his cursing of the fig tree. And the third is his cleansing of the temple.

00:05:04.768 --> 00:05:09.312
He rides into Jerusalem to the cheers of the people.

00:05:09.280 --> 00:05:18.432
Jerusalem was filled with travelers from all over the world come to celebrate the Passover. He grabs their attention with the cult of

00:05:18.176 --> 00:05:21.376
and the Paw Branches and the shouts of Hosanna.

00:05:21.216 --> 00:05:27.328
And here Jesus fulfills the prophecy of Zechariah 9:9 which says,

00:05:27.296 --> 00:05:33.728
Rejoice greatly, o daughter of Zion, shout aloud, o daughter of Jerusalem.

00:05:33.504 --> 00:05:34.880
Behold.

00:05:34.656 --> 00:05:37.184
Your king is coming to you.

00:05:36.960 --> 00:05:40.864
Righteous and having salvation is he

00:05:40.704 --> 00:05:44.576
Humble and mounted on a donkey, on a colt,

00:05:44.544 --> 00:05:46.176
The fall of a donkey.

00:05:46.432 --> 00:05:48.768
That's what the people are shouting.

00:05:48.512 --> 00:05:55.808
Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord blessed is the coming kingdom of our father David and

00:05:55.648 --> 00:05:56.832
Jesus

00:05:56.608 --> 00:06:02.304
is claiming to be the heir of David, the rightful king of Israel.

00:06:02.240 --> 00:06:10.464
Now, don't forget, he knows why he's come to Jerusalem to be delivered up, mocked, beaten, and killed.

00:06:10.304 --> 00:06:20.352
to die for our sins as our Savior. But He wants us to know the one who dies as our Savior is the rightful Lord of all.

00:06:19.872 --> 00:06:20.832
Of all.

00:06:20.640 --> 00:06:23.776
He is King David's greater son

00:06:23.776 --> 00:06:25.376
The king of kings.

00:06:25.312 --> 00:06:26.976
and Lord of Lords.

00:06:27.456 --> 00:06:29.024
And then we see

00:06:28.960 --> 00:06:31.104
The curse of the fig tree

00:06:31.104 --> 00:06:32.960
Jesus is hungry.

00:06:32.736 --> 00:06:34.336
Now consider that.

00:06:34.304 --> 00:06:43.680
He can be touched with the feelings of our infirmity. He tasted pain and weakness and weariness and hunger and thirst.

00:06:43.808 --> 00:06:47.040
When you share your burdens with him in prayer,

00:06:46.848 --> 00:06:49.152
He knows what you mean.

00:06:49.120 --> 00:06:51.136
From personal experience.

00:06:51.808 --> 00:06:58.048
Now the fig tree was all leaves and no fruit, as the cowboys might say, all had no cattle.

00:06:58.112 --> 00:07:00.640
Much like Jerusalem herself,

00:07:00.416 --> 00:07:02.816
The Jewish people in his day.

00:07:02.528 --> 00:07:06.528
There was an appearance of life, but no fruit for God.

00:07:06.240 --> 00:07:07.776
2.

00:07:07.552 --> 00:07:09.280
Without repentance.

00:07:09.088 --> 00:07:10.688
Religiosity.

00:07:10.496 --> 00:07:12.608
Without genuine love.

00:07:12.544 --> 00:07:15.520
There was much hypocrisy

00:07:15.392 --> 00:07:17.280
And little humility.

00:07:17.088 --> 00:07:20.000
Especially among her teachers and leaders.

00:07:20.096 --> 00:07:21.408
Jesus,

00:07:21.120 --> 00:07:23.136
Curse the fig tree,

00:07:22.944 --> 00:07:27.744
As a parable for Israel, should they not bear fruit by believing in him?

00:07:27.872 --> 00:07:29.952
Reject your king and savior,

00:07:29.856 --> 00:07:32.864
and you'll never bear fruit for God.

00:07:32.832 --> 00:07:34.368
Was its message.

00:07:35.040 --> 00:07:36.800
In the third event,

00:07:36.704 --> 00:07:40.384
Jesus cleanses the temple of thieves.

00:07:40.320 --> 00:07:46.208
The money changers are making bank on the need of the people to buy livestock.

00:07:46.336 --> 00:07:49.440
And the need of the poor to buy pigeons.

00:07:49.184 --> 00:07:51.136
For temple sacrifices.

00:07:51.072 --> 00:07:54.304
And it makes Jesus hot with anger.

00:07:54.368 --> 00:07:58.944
The temple ought to be the place where people meet with God.

00:07:58.688 --> 00:08:01.920
where people pray to God, where priests

00:08:01.664 --> 00:08:08.352
Pastor the people not a place where irreverent businessmen trade goods for profit

00:08:09.216 --> 00:08:10.208
Now,

00:08:10.048 --> 00:08:13.568
Unsurprisingly, people are sometimes shocked

00:08:13.440 --> 00:08:15.424
At the behavior of Jesus.

00:08:15.296 --> 00:08:20.160
He takes a colt that's never been ridden and passes a message to the owner.

00:08:20.608 --> 00:08:22.208
I need it.

00:08:22.048 --> 00:08:29.888
He makes barren a fig tree and people get stirred up asking if innocent creatures suffered needlessly.

00:08:29.856 --> 00:08:39.904
He whips at money changers and drives them out overturning the tables and messing up their businesses so much for gentle Jesus meek and

00:08:39.424 --> 00:08:40.768
180 miles.

00:08:40.736 --> 00:08:43.104
Here he is in strength.

00:08:43.040 --> 00:08:45.184
and righteous indignation.

00:08:45.792 --> 00:08:50.912
So then the spiritually blind chief priests and scribes and elders ask,

00:08:50.656 --> 00:08:55.648
By what authority are you doing these things? And who gave you this authority to do them?

00:08:56.288 --> 00:08:58.944
Now, that's actually a good question.

00:08:58.976 --> 00:09:05.376
Though they don't really want the true answer, which is why Jesus asks them about John's authority.

00:09:05.184 --> 00:09:09.056
If John was the prophet from God,

00:09:08.960 --> 00:09:12.032
And John said he wasn't worried the

00:09:11.712 --> 00:09:15.296
To stoop down and untie the sandals of Jesus.

00:09:15.232 --> 00:09:17.120
Then who does that make Jesus?

00:09:17.216 --> 00:09:27.264
If John isn't worthy to do even the least part of what the lowest servant would do, even untie the sandal, let alone touch or wash the feet,

00:09:26.784 --> 00:09:27.392
Eat.

00:09:27.392 --> 00:09:29.408
Then who is Jesus?

00:09:29.696 --> 00:09:31.712
Well, he's more than mere man.

00:09:31.552 --> 00:09:41.600
He's God in human flesh, king of kings. That's why Passover pilgrims worship him. That's why nature obeys him. That's why he

00:09:41.120 --> 00:09:45.088
That's why he's zealous that his house be a house of prayer.

00:09:44.864 --> 00:09:46.784
And not a den of robbers.

00:09:46.784 --> 00:09:48.800
And since he's God,

00:09:49.280 --> 00:09:52.224
Your faith in him is not misplaced.

00:09:52.192 --> 00:09:55.552
Your forgiveness comes from him.

00:09:55.648 --> 00:09:59.264
Your prayers should be in His name.

00:09:59.424 --> 00:10:03.040
And your adoration be of him.

00:10:04.000 --> 00:10:06.528
May God make it so. Let's pray.

00:10:06.976 --> 00:10:11.616
Father in heaven, your son is king and savior.

00:10:11.392 --> 00:10:13.472
Have mercy upon us.

00:10:13.472 --> 00:10:15.072
In his name.

00:10:15.104 --> 00:10:16.320
Amen.

00:10:16.544 --> 00:10:18.592
Well, thank you for listening in.

00:10:18.400 --> 00:10:20.544
And I hope you'll join me next time.
